    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Identify B in the following series of reaction</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO} \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{MgX}} A \\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{HOH}} B$$</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "2-propanol"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "1-propanol"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "ethanol"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "None of these"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The given reaction sequence involves a Grignard reaction followed by an acidic workup. Let's break down each step:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Step 1: Grignard Reaction</strong></p>\n\n<p>The Grignard reagent, $$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{MgX}$$, is a strong nucleophile. It attacks the electrophilic carbonyl carbon of acetaldehyde ($$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$$). This results in the formation of an alkoxide intermediate, which upon acidic workup (with water, $$\\mathrm{HOH}$$) gives the corresponding alcohol.</p>\n\n<p>The reaction can be represented as follows:</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO} + \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{MgX} \\longrightarrow \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH(OMgX)CH}_3 $$</p>\n\n<p><strong>Step 2: Acidic Workup</strong></p>\n\n<p>The alkoxide intermediate reacts with water to form the final product, an alcohol. The reaction can be represented as follows:</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH(OMgX)CH}_3 + \\mathrm{HOH} \\longrightarrow \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH(OH)CH}_3 + \\mathrm{MgXOH} $$</p>\n\n<p>The product formed is <strong>2-propanol</strong>. Therefore, B is <strong>2-propanol</strong>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Correct Answer:</strong> Option A</p>\n\n<p></p>",
